1
00:00:01,840 --> 00:00:04,560
DALEK EMPEROR: Purify the Earth with fire.

2
00:00:04,640 --> 00:00:09,200
The planet will become my temple
and we shall rise.

3
00:00:09,600 --> 00:00:12,080
You are the heathen.

4
00:00:12,160 --> 00:00:16,160
You will be exterminated.

5
00:00:16,240 --> 00:00:18,920
DALEKS: Exterminate. Exterminate.

6
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:21,440
Tardis materialising.

7
00:00:27,720 --> 00:00:29,720
I looked into the Tardis.

8
00:00:30,720 --> 00:00:32,560
And the Tardis looked into me.

9
00:00:32,640 --> 00:00:36,800
You've got the entire vortex
running through your head, you're gonna burn!

10
00:00:36,880 --> 00:00:39,680
I can see the whole of time and space.

11
00:00:39,760 --> 00:00:43,560
Every single atom of your existence
and I divide them.

12
00:00:46,560 --> 00:00:48,280
The Time War ends.

13
00:00:48,360 --> 00:00:52,000
I cannot die.

14
00:00:58,440 --> 00:01:01,240
-My head. ..
-Come here.

15
00:01:01,320 --> 00:01:05,360
-...is killing me.
-I think you need a doctor.

16
00:01:19,680 --> 00:01:21,440
-Doctor!
-Stay away!

17
00:01:22,440 --> 00:01:24,240
Doctor, tell me what's going on.

18
00:01:24,320 --> 00:01:28,280
I absorbed all the energy of the time vortex
and no one's meant to do that.

19
00:01:28,360 --> 00:01:32,920
Time Lords have this little trick.
It's sort of a way of cheating death.

20
00:01:49,280 --> 00:01:51,080
Hello, okay.

21
00:01:54,400 --> 00:01:57,200
New teeth, that's weird. So, where was I?

22
00:01:58,040 --> 00:02:00,920
Oh, that's right, Barcelona!

23
00:02:38,880 --> 00:02:40,800
600 pm.

24
00:02:40,880 --> 00:02:46,000
Tuesday, October, 5006,

25
00:02:46,080 --> 00:02:48,040
on the way to Barcelona.

26
00:02:48,120 --> 00:02:50,280
Now then, what do I look like?

27
00:02:50,360 --> 00:02:54,240
No, no, no, no, no, don't tell me. Let's see.

28
00:02:54,320 --> 00:02:58,600
Two legs, two arms, two hands,
slight weakness in the dorsal tubercle.

29
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:00,840
Hair! I'm not bald.

30
00:03:00,920 --> 00:03:05,000
Ooh, big hair. Sideburns, I've got sideburns!

31
00:03:05,080 --> 00:03:08,640
Really bad skin. Little bit thinner, that's weird.

32
00:03:08,720 --> 00:03:10,560
Give me time. I'll get used to it.

33
00:03:10,640 --> 00:03:13,560
I have got a mole.

34
00:03:13,640 --> 00:03:17,320
I can feel it.
Between the shoulder blades, there's a mole.

35
00:03:18,120 --> 00:03:21,920
That's all right. Love the mole.
Go on, then, tell me.

36
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:23,720
What do you think?

37
00:03:24,960 --> 00:03:27,160
-Who are you?
-I'm the Doctor.

38
00:03:28,280 --> 00:03:30,200
No. Where is he?

39
00:03:31,080 --> 00:03:33,120
Where's the Doctor? What've you done to him?

40
00:03:33,200 --> 00:03:36,440
You saw me, I changed. Right in front of you.

41
00:03:36,520 --> 00:03:41,920
I saw him sort of explode
and then you replaced him,

42
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:47,920
like a teleport or a transmat
or a body swap or something.

43
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:54,640
You're not fooling me.

44
00:03:55,240 --> 00:03:59,280
I've seen all sorts of things, nanogenes, Gelth,

45
00:04:00,200 --> 00:04:01,960
Slitheen.

46
00:04:03,560 --> 00:04:05,600
Oh, my God, are you Slitheen?

47
00:04:06,640 --> 00:04:08,640
I'm not a Slitheen.

48
00:04:08,720 --> 00:04:13,160
Send him back.
I'm warning you, send the Doctor back right now.

49
00:04:13,240 --> 00:04:15,920
Rose, it's me. Honestly, it's me.

50
00:04:17,440 --> 00:04:19,040
I was dying.

51
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:23,560
To save my own life, I changed my body.
Every single cell, but still me.

52
00:04:25,960 --> 00:04:27,400
You can't be.

53
00:04:28,160 --> 00:04:30,360
Then how can I remember this?

54
00:04:31,080 --> 00:04:33,560
The very first word I ever said to you,

55
00:04:33,640 --> 00:04:37,000
trapped in that cellar,
surrounded by shop-window dummies.

56
00:04:37,080 --> 00:04:39,680
Ooh, such a long time ago.

57
00:04:41,040 --> 00:04:46,040
I took your hand, I said one word. Just one word.

58
00:04:46,120 --> 00:04:48,400
I said, "Run."

59
00:04:51,440 --> 00:04:52,640
Doctor.

60
00:04:53,440 --> 00:04:55,280
-Hello.
-Oh, my God.

61
00:04:55,360 --> 00:04:58,120
And we never stopped, did we?
All across the universe.

62
00:04:58,200 --> 00:05:01,120
Running, running, running.
And one time we had to hop. Do you remember?

63
00:05:01,200 --> 00:05:04,760
Hopping for our lives. Yeah? All that hopping.

64
00:05:04,840 --> 00:05:07,040
Remember hopping for your life? Yeah?

65
00:05:07,120 --> 00:05:10,480
Hop. Where they... No?

66
00:05:12,640 --> 00:05:14,640
-Can you change back?
-Do you want me to?

67
00:05:14,720 --> 00:05:16,040
-Yeah.
-Oh.

68
00:05:16,880 --> 00:05:18,520
-Can you?
-No.

69
00:05:21,320 --> 00:05:24,280
-Do you want to leave?
-Do you want me to leave?

70
00:05:24,360 --> 00:05:28,360
No, but your choice, if you want to go home.

71
00:05:31,480 --> 00:05:33,120
Cancel Barcelona.

72
00:05:33,880 --> 00:05:36,840
Change to London, the Powell Estate.

73
00:05:39,160 --> 00:05:42,840
Let's say, 24th December.
Consider it a Christmas present.

74
00:05:46,240 --> 00:05:47,520
There.

75
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:58,320
-I'm going home?
-Up to you.

76
00:05:58,400 --> 00:06:00,960
Back to your mum. It's all waiting.

77
00:06:01,920 --> 00:06:05,560
Fish and chips, sausage and mash,
beans on toast. No, Christmas, turkey!

78
00:06:05,640 --> 00:06:10,240
Although, having met your mother,
nut loaf would be more appropriate.

79
00:06:11,880 --> 00:06:13,920
-Was that a smile?
-No.

80
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:15,280
That was a smile.

81
00:06:15,360 --> 00:06:17,200
-No, it wasn't.
-You smiled.

82
00:06:17,280 --> 00:06:20,120
-No, I didn't.
-Oh, come on, all I did was change. I didn't...

83
00:06:22,920 --> 00:06:24,520
-wWhat?
-I said...

84
00:06:27,640 --> 00:06:28,920
DOCTOR: Uh-oh.

85
00:06:30,640 --> 00:06:32,120
Are you all right?

86
00:06:36,160 --> 00:06:37,600
What's that?

87
00:06:38,920 --> 00:06:41,280
The change is going a bit wrong. I'm all...

88
00:06:42,760 --> 00:06:44,960
Look, maybe we should go back.

89
00:06:45,040 --> 00:06:47,440
Let's go and find Captain Jack.
He'll know what to do.

90
00:06:47,520 --> 00:06:50,960
Ah, he's busy.
He's got plenty to do rebuilding the Earth.

91
00:06:51,480 --> 00:06:53,320
I haven't used this one in years.

92
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:58,440
-What are you doing?
-Putting on a bit of speed, that's it.

93
00:06:58,520 --> 00:07:02,040
My beautiful ship, come on. Faster, atta girl.

94
00:07:03,080 --> 00:07:06,040
What do you think? Faster?
Do you wanna break the time limit?

95
00:07:06,120 --> 00:07:09,000
-Stop it!
-Ah, don't be so dull. Let's have a bit of fun.

96
00:07:09,080 --> 00:07:11,520
Let's rip through that vortex.

97
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:13,360
Regeneration's going wrong.

98
00:07:13,440 --> 00:07:15,680
(MUMBLING)

99
00:07:15,760 --> 00:07:17,640
(GROANING) My head.

100
00:07:17,720 --> 00:07:20,440
Faster! Let's open those engines all the way.

101
00:07:20,520 --> 00:07:21,720
(ALARM BLARING)

102
00:07:21,800 --> 00:07:24,680
-What's that?
-We're gonna crash-land.

103
00:07:25,440 --> 00:07:27,920
-Well, then do something!
-Too late!

104
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:32,680
-You're gonna kill us!
-Hold on tight, here we go!

105
00:07:32,880 --> 00:07:34,360
Christmas Eve.

